from left to right. So on the left hand side is the home and this is where smart meters would sit

00:05:28.480 --> 00:05:35.600
and smart meters are installed to enable people to have greater functionality at the local end of

00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:46.239
the electricity market. So within an electric meter and a gas meter you'd also see in-home

00:05:46.239 --> 00:05:51.359
display and this allows the user to see how much electricity or gas they're using or what tariff

00:05:51.359 --> 00:05:55.519
they're on or any interesting information. But there's also a number of other smart devices that

00:05:55.519 --> 00:06:00.880
would be in the home including prepayment devices and devices to enable electric vehicles.

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:07.440
All of this is installed within the home and that's what one of our day jobs is to ensure that

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:13.760
the installation of these meters takes place and these devices communicate via what's called a

00:06:13.760 --> 00:06:19.679
comms hub. So on the left hand side within the home all those devices and there's a comms hub and that

00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:26.640
allows communication both within the home but also via a wide area network back out to our users.

00:06:27.279 --> 00:06:32.880
And if you look at the the middle piece there that describes our network. So we've got communication

00:06:33.679 --> 00:06:40.000
service providers, data service providers and a whole host more. There's eight shown there but in

