map of all the installs just on one day. So that was the number of meters and where they were installed

00:07:40.720 --> 00:07:47.519
one day and actually this is taken from one of our applications that we utilize.

00:07:48.799 --> 00:07:54.959
That means we've got an ever-growing base of devices out there that are communicating across

00:07:54.959 --> 00:08:02.000
our network growing by about 20,000 a day and that means the volume of data we're dealing with

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:08.239
is growing and you can see there just last month we were over half a billion records in a month

00:08:08.239 --> 00:08:14.959
that we need to process and analyze to provide results to our 100 plus customers and this creates

00:08:14.959 --> 00:08:21.040
a complex data set. There's all the transactional data but on top of that there's the data that

00:08:21.040 --> 00:08:28.399
supports those transactions, the inventory data. And why does this get complicated? Well smart meters

00:08:28.959 --> 00:08:35.359
have protocols that allow them to communicate and there's 127 different types of message that can be

00:08:35.359 --> 00:08:42.239
sent across the network. Those messages might vary from a meter read to a firmware update or a

00:08:42.239 --> 00:08:48.400
certificate swap and all those messages come across our network. They vary in size and some of them

00:08:48.400 --> 00:08:53.919
have to be sent in a specific order to allow them to be processed. So there's a complicated series

00:08:53.919 --> 00:09:00.080
of messages that goes across the network. We mentioned earlier about our infrastructure is

00:09:00.080 --> 00:09:07.679
a complicated technical solution that means that the data that maps to it is complicated and we

00:09:07.679 --> 00:09:14.320
have to map that all together. And finally there's our users. How are they using the solution? They're

00:09:14.320 --> 00:09:20.960
all using it differently so we have to understand what the difference between our 100 plus users and

00:09:20.960 --> 00:09:26.960
how they're using it and how we report on that data to them and to our governing bodies and

00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:37.359
